<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">AI Content Editing Guide</h1>

<p class="govuk-body-l">
  Learn how to use AI-powered features to write and simplify content in LocalGov Drupal.
</p>

{# What you'll learn summary #}
<div class="govuk-inset-text ndx-guide-summary">
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-s">What you'll learn</h2>
  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>How to access and use the AI Write feature</li>
    <li>How to simplify text to plain English</li>
    <li>Tips for writing effective prompts</li>
    <li>Common council content use cases</li>
  </ul>
</div>

{# Introduction Section #}
<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What is AI-powered content editing?</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  LocalGov Drupal includes AI features powered by Amazon Bedrock that help content editors:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>Generate draft content</strong> from a simple prompt</li>
  <li><strong>Simplify existing text</strong> to plain English (reading age 9)</li>
  <li><strong>Save time</strong> on routine content tasks</li>
  <li><strong>Maintain consistency</strong> across council communications</li>
</ul>

<div class="govuk-warning-text">
  <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
  <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
    <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Important</span>
    AI-generated content should always be reviewed and edited before publishing.
    The AI is a writing assistant, not a replacement for human judgement.
  </strong>
</div>

{# Available Features Section #}
<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Available AI features</h2>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <div class="ndx-feature-card">
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">AI Write</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        Generate new content from a prompt. Perfect for drafting service pages,
        guides, news articles, and more.
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
        <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">In CKEditor toolbar</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <div class="ndx-feature-card">
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Simplify to Plain English</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        Select existing text and simplify it. Great for making complex
        information accessible to all residents.
      </p>
      <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
        <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">Accessibility focused</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{# Getting Started Section #}
<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Getting started</h2>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Accessing the AI toolbar</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  The AI features are available in any content edit form that uses the CKEditor:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Navigate to any content page</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Go to Content &gt; Add content, or edit an existing page
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Find the Body field</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The rich text editor with the AI button is in the main Body field
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Look for the AI button</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The AI button appears in the CKEditor toolbar (lightning bolt icon)
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

